products.title: Ayotte 14" x 21" Cocktail Drum with AXIS Pedal
products.body_html:
Ayotte 14" x 21" Cocktail Drum with AXIS Pedal

This might possibly be the ultimate cocktail drum. Made by Ayotte in Vancouver during the 90's. This drum features a tall Ayotte shell with classic wood hoops and a Satin Ebony finish. The bass drum side features the best Reverse pedal you can find made by AXIS. It is basically an adapted Slave side from a double pedal. The actual single pedal can be used on a kit as a normal AXIS pedal. 

Snare is a standard half snare that pushes against the back side of the top batter with a muffler style adjustment on the outside of the drum.

These Ayotte Cocktail drums are very rare items.

products.title: British Drum Company Lounge Club Kit
products.body_html:
Welcome British Drum Company to our line up.

Lounge Club kit 22/12/16 Shell pack in Wiltshire White, a nicely figured outer ply of Scandinavian birch.

Lounge Series drums are formulated from a combination of 9 ply Mahogany and Scandinavian Birch which has been cross laminated and cold-press moulded into a shell only 5.5mm thick. This results in super-strong, super-thin shells that produces a warm and complex tone. Like our Legend Series these are precision hand-crafted drums and are incredibly versatile. The addition of Mahogany and 30 degree round-over bearing edges add a tremendous darker warmth and projection synonymous with the best vintage kits. These drums share the same wide tuning range to suit any musical situation producing low fat tones when tuned down and a brighter warmth when tuned up.

products.title: C & C Drum Company 12th and Vine Be Bop
products.body_html:
Beautiful hand crafted made in USA drums. 
Inspired by the great American drums from the 50s, 60s and 70s, the 12th & Vine features a 5 ply shell with a Poplar Core, 7 Ply Maple Reinforcement Rings and our Los Angeles bearing edge. The Poplar core warms up the shell and absorbs unwanted overtones, while providing a sound equally suitable for live and studio use. This line comes standard with stick saver hoops, vintage “fold out” bass drum spurs, and our new single-ended Deco lug.
Mahogany/Poplar/Mahogany: A reference to the classic sounds of the 1950s, our Mahogany/Poplar ply configuration is one of the warmest Gladstone Shell Configurations. Depth and character are more pronounced in quieter, softer musical settings while fat, round tones come out when things get a bit louder.

products.title: Canopus Club Kit 3pc - used
products.body_html:
Killer sounding super portable Canopus Club Kit in Champagne Sparkle wrap.

  • 15 x 12 bass drum with riser
  • 10 x 7 rack tom with bass drum mount
  • 14 x 12 floor tom

The Club Kit was the first series CANOPUS introduced, and later it became the foundation of the current R.F.M. series. The Club Kit is characterized by the 15 inch bass drum, which is the smallest size that allows the use of a bass drum beater. Our challenge was to gain enough bass drum sound out of the smallest shell.
Although a 15 inch drum is usually only considered for a tom-tom, we succeeded in gaining a surprisingly rich and low bass drum sound. People trying the Club Kit for the first time are impressed by the rich sound from its compact size.

To achieve the rich sound on such a small drum, we use a standard tom-tom head. The difference between the bass drum head and the tom-tom head is the shape of the collar. On a 15 inch head, a standard bass drum collar is much too strong. It absorbs the energy on the head and even muffles the drums natural resonance. After comparing a bass drum style head with a standard tom tom head, we found the latter to be much more resonant on such a small shell. This is a small example of the attention to detail that CANOPUS brings to the table. Rather than relying on simple theory or common sense, we take the time to think outside of the box to ensure our products achieve the ideal sound we strive for and our customers demand.
